{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "Fixes #78\r\n\r\nAn AABB can overlap multiple frustum planes and still not be inside of it. This fixes the issue by adding two more checks to `Frustum::Contains(Box)` when there are multiple overlapping planes. The tests have been expanded to check these cases.\r\n\r\nThe unit tests still don't have 100% of the AABB overlap possibilities, but I think the missing cases work. For future reference these are missing (likely more I haven't thought of):\r\n\r\n * large AABB behind frustum overlapping near plane and 1 or 2 side planes\r\n * large AABB in front or behind frustum overlapping 4 side planes\r\n * large AABB overlapping 5 or 6 planes (requires frustum pose to be rotated)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Fixes <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/issues/78/frustum-incorrectly-reports-that-it\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Frustum incorrectly reports that it contains a box\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#78</s></a></p>\n<p>An AABB can overlap multiple frustum planes and still not be inside of it. This fixes the issue by adding two more checks to <code>Frustum::Contains(Box)</code> when there are multiple overlapping planes. The tests have been expanded to check these cases.</p>\n<p>The unit tests still don't have 100% of the AABB overlap possibilities, but I think the missing cases work. For future reference these are missing (likely more I haven't thought of):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>large AABB behind frustum overlapping near plane and 1 or 2 side planes</li>\n<li>large AABB in front or behind frustum overlapping 4 side planes</li>\n<li>large AABB overlapping 5 or 6 planes (requires frustum pose to be rotated)</li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Fixes Frustum falsly reporting it contains AABB in some cases", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Fixes Frustum falsly reporting it contains AABB in some cases</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Fixes #78\r\n\r\nAn AABB can overlap multiple fr